TopicTitle: Unknown issue is causing debug window to lag me out.

Articles.Content:
As title says, Only thing I have to go off of is the lag im getting from the debug console window spamming these messages.

Packing vessel for orbit

Unpacking vessel

Packing vessel for orbit

Unpacking vessel

Packing vessel for orbit

Unpacking vessel

Packing vessel for orbit

Unpacking vessel

 

It goes on and and on, literally once I get into orbit I go from a stable 50fps to 10-15 or less depending on if im on the dark side of a planet or light side

Heres my mod list

Check the log files, they provide much more information:

I can’t think of anything that might be causing this issue, but the logs would help.

Logs only report 

 


Packing Starship for orbit
 

KerbalJointReinforcement: extents could not be properly built for part 'Drill-O-Matic' Mining Excavator
 
(Filename: C:\buildslave\unity\build\Runtime/Export/Debug/Debug.bindings.h Line: 35)

KerbalJointReinforcement: extents could not be properly built for part 'Drill-O-Matic' Mining Excavator
 
(Filename: C:\buildslave\unity\build\Runtime/Export/Debug/Debug.bindings.h Line: 35)

[UIMasterController]: ShowUI
 
(Filename: C:\buildslave\unity\build\Runtime/Export/Debug/Debug.bindings.h Line: 35)

Packing Starship for orbit
 
(Filename: C:\buildslave\unity\build\Runtime/Export/Debug/Debug.bindings.h Line: 35)

Unpacking Starship
 
(Filename: C:\buildslave\unity\build\Runtime/Export/Debug/Debug.bindings.h Line: 35)

...

Which doesn't help much,

Some more information i just found, this happens typically between 72,000km and 120km around kerbin or while orbiting kerbin, for some reason when i activate my engines it stops but as soon as i throttle back down to 0 it starts to spam again, then its fine for a few seconds until i reach around 600km to 800k then it does it again... seriously I have no clue what is causing this lol. it happens in waves, itll be fine for a few then hits hard again.

Here is the log for the most recent test flight, https://www.dropbox.com/s/700frgzqomz2qsj/Player.log?dl=0

Note this is a 25mb file for a 5 minute flight. lol
It came down to a corrupted save file, after starting new save file issue stopped, RIP Vcam Space Center 1243 hours.
I'm having this same issue.  But its only with larger vessels.  Just because starting a new save file fixes it doesn't necessarily mean its a corrupted install.
@VCamProbe hey I tried it out in a brand new save and it still happens.  Its not a corrupted save, its something on that vessel.
This may be irrelevant, but sometimes looking at terrain can cause high part count vessels to glitch out.
